  <thing id="deiEMPHoru" name="Horus" description="The hawk-headed god called Horus is the youngest and most powerful in a long line of elder gods. Horus rose to prominence after striking down his uncle to avenge the death of his father. His older relatives have since declined in prominence and power, accepting Horus as the primary representative of their divine family.\n\nThough best known for his vengeful nature, Horus is compassionate towards the innocent and towards individuals who are truly repentant for their past misdeeds. Those who have been targeted by Horus&apos;s avenging clerics are often surprised to learn that services to Horus make little mention of vengeance and war, focusing instead upon civility, compassion, and personal responsibility.\n\nMost priests of Horus are clerics or inquisitors, but Horus also sponsors a fair number of paladins among the Eagle Clans. Unlike most other creatures, Eagle Clan saurians are able to serve as paladins while maintaining a chaotic good alignment, a blessing bestowed upon their clan by Horus himself. At the GM&apos;s option, certain non-Eagles that earn the favor of Horus may receive a similar boon.\n\n{b}The Eye of Ra:{/b} Horus is one of several deities that share the title, Eye of Ra. When the Eye of Ra title passes to Horus, the hawk god becomes an avatar of the personified Sun for as long as he retains the title.\n\nOther deities which periodically serve as the Eye of Ra include: Amon, god of the Goats Clans; Athor, goddess of the Ox Clans; Ishtar, goddess of the Cat Clans; Sobek, god of the Crocodile Clans; and Uraeus, god of the Snake Clans." compset="Deity" uniqueness="unique">
    <fieldval field="deiEpithet" value="The Avenger"/>
    <fieldval field="deiPortfol" value="God of liberty, justice, and freedom"/>
    <fieldval field="deiSymbol" value="Heiroglyphic depiction of a hawk"/>
    <usesource source="EMPRaptor"/>
    <tag group="AllowDom" tag="cdSun" name="Sun" abbrev="Sun"/>
    <tag group="WepProf" tag="wKhopesh" name="Khopesh" abbrev="Khopesh"/>
    <tag group="AllowDom" tag="cdGlory"/>
    <tag group="AllowDom" tag="cdGood"/>
    <tag group="AllowDom" tag="cdLiberat"/>
    <tag group="AllowDom" tag="cdWar"/>
    <tag group="AlignTemp" tag="ChaotGood"/>
    <tag group="DeityCat" tag="AnimalRace"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="trEMPHaga" name="Haga" description="Two-headed eagles known as hagas are imperious beasts. They are capable of fighting on two fronts at once but are prone to internal conflict. If you select this heraldic symbol in place of your first trait, you gain Two-Weapon Fighting as a bonus feat, but you take a –1 penalty on all Will saves." compset="Trait" summary="Gain Two-Weapon Fighting, but -1 to Will saves." uniqueness="unique">
